ðŸ”µ What is ORM?

ORM = Object-Relational Mapping

It is a technique that:

Maps database tables â†” C# classes

Maps rows â†” objects

Maps columns â†” properties

Instead of writing SQL like this:

SELECT * FROM Users WHERE Id = 1


You write C#:

var user = context.Users.FirstOrDefault(u => u.Id == 1);

ðŸ”µ Entity Framework = Microsoft ORM for .NET

Entity Framework (especially Entity Framework Core) is:

Developed by Microsoft

Used in .NET applications

Converts LINQ queries into SQL

Tracks changes automatically

Handles CRUD operations

