ðŸ”¥ Why EF is an ORM

Because it:

Maps objects â†” relational database

Handles relationships (One-to-Many, Many-to-Many)

Manages database schema (Migrations)

Tracks object state (Added, Modified, Deleted)

ðŸ”µ Advantages

Less SQL writing

Faster development

Database abstraction

Change tracking

LINQ support

ðŸ”´ Limitations

Performance overhead in complex queries

Sometimes raw SQL is faster

Needs optimization for large-scale systems

